{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8be723cd-e52f-4fcc-820a-122fce98ae94","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, you just need to **remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n-   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**That's it.** Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.4+, Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the **default** runner. Setting `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` was explicitly opting out of it — removing that line opts you back in.\n\n### What changes at runtime\n\n| | VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Run tests | `dotnet test` | `dotnet test` (still works) |\n| Test binary | not directly runnable | directly runnable (`./YourTests`) |\n| CLI args | `--filter` etc. | `--filter` still works; new options like `--list-tests` |\n\n### Watch out for\n- **Custom `.runsettings`** — most settings carry over, but review for deprecated nodes.\n- **`dotnet test` CLI flags** — a few VSTest-specific flags (e.g. `--logger \"trx\"`) change syntax; use `dotnet test -- --help` to see new options.\n- **CI pipelines** — update any scripts that parse VSTest-specific output or use `/p:UseVSTest=true`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4eacb2b4-2e37-4c30-a8b5-b2cdb5e7ffeb","outputTokens":359,"requestId":"7C1F:DF52E:2767FE1:2B75781:69F93FA3"},"id":"82f64a15-da48-42ab-8200-a7d9db653e68","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:54:08.026Z","parentId":"81cda96e-7cc4-44b5-8df1-4a4ef288274f"}
